lego:evidence  a  owl:AnnotationProperty .

gomodel:SYNGO_3131  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig.2: \"PDZ2 of SAP90/PSD-95 is able to precipitate a chimeric EphrinB1/Sema4F protein\"\n\nFig.3: \"EphrinB1/Sema4F, but not EphrinB1/Sema4FΔ, is able to translocate SAP90/PSD-95 from the cytosol to the membrane. \"\n\nFig.4: \"Sema4F immunoreactivity is present in synaptosome fractions and enriched in post-synaptic density fractions from rat brain\"\n\nFig.5: \"Colocalization of Sema4F with SAP90/PSD-95 and synapsin1 in cultured hippocampal neurons\"\n\n- Based on the known transmembrane topology of the protein, the \"integral component of ... membrane\" term was chosen.. Experimental description: - \"Hippocampal neurons from new-born (P0-P4) Wistar rats ...\"\n- \"Sema4F immunoreactivity is present in synaptosome fractions and enriched in post-synaptic density fractions from rat brain\"\n- \"To construct EphrinB1/Sema4F the cytoplasmic and transmembrane domain of Sema4F (amino acids 670-777, nucleotides 2088-2412) was amplified using the primer TTCTTC AACTCCAAGACCGTTGTGGGGGCTGGGCTG and the primer up from a cDNA clone representing almost the complete coding sequence of mouse Sema4F isolated from a screen of a mouse brain cDNA library (Clontech). \"" , "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099061 replaced by GO:0098839" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0593-3443" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_3131" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

